---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import LoopsDiagram from '../components/LoopsDiagram.astro';
import AltitudesDiagram from '../components/AltitudesDiagram.astro';
---
<Base>
  <h1>My Alicia</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Most AI tools are built for everyone. My Alicia is an AI teammate
    built for me.
  </p>

  <p>
    What she says and why she says it is private. It's based on what
    I read, the notes I take, the questions I ask. But how she works
    and how she grows is yours to take and adapt however you want.
    My Alicia can be Your [Name].
  </p>

  <h2>Three depths of attention</h2>

  <p>
    She runs on three loops at three timescales. She listens in the
    moment. She notices over hours. And she comes to know over days
    and weeks. The slower loops watch the faster ones, so patterns
    surface on their own.
  </p>

  <div class="figure">
    <LoopsDiagram />
    <p class="caption">Three depths of attention — Listen, Notice, Know — over a shared memory substrate.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>From notes to wisdom</h2>

  <p>
    Knowledge moves through her in altitudes. Daily inputs metabolize
    into synthesis. Synthesis metabolizes into wisdom. External
    research keeps the loop open to new authors and viewpoints, so
    she doesn't only reflect what's already in the vault.
  </p>

  <div class="figure">
    <AltitudesDiagram />
    <p class="caption">From notes to wisdom — the altitudes of knowing.</p>
  </div>

  <hr class="rule" />

  <h2>For designers and builders</h2>

  <p>
    The contribution surface is what we call <strong>awareness primitives</strong> —
    small, opinionated modules that turn some slice of life into structured
    memory the loops can metabolize: a reading-pattern primitive, a
    calendar-rhythm primitive, a relationship-graph primitive.
  </p>

  <p>
    Think of contributions as <em>designing perception</em>. That's
    what design practice needs to expand into in the agentic era.
  </p>

  <hr class="rule" />

  <h2>Try it</h2>

  <p>
    <code>pipx install myalicia &amp;&amp; myalicia init</code>
  </p>

  <p>
    The init flow is more than configuration — it's a guided introduction
    to relationship-shaped AI. Each setup step is paired with a one-screen
    explanation of which loop it activates and why.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a class="cta" href="https://github.com/mrdaemoni/myalicia">View on GitHub →</a>
  </p>
</Base>
